# Lightweight collision/hydrodynamics hull for the BlueROV2.
# The visual mesh (BlueROV2.obj, ~973k verts) is far too heavy to use for the
# physics/buoyancy integration that Stonefish runs every simulation step, so a
# simple box approximating the vehicle's displaced volume is used instead.
# Body frame: x=forward, y=starboard, z=down.  Dimensions 0.35 x 0.28 x 0.13 m
# => volume ~0.0127 m^3 => ~12.7 kgf of buoyancy (tuned against mass in the .scn).
o BlueROV2_hull
v -0.175 -0.140 -0.065
v  0.175 -0.140 -0.065
v  0.175  0.140 -0.065
v -0.175  0.140 -0.065
v -0.175 -0.140  0.065
v  0.175 -0.140  0.065
v  0.175  0.140  0.065
v -0.175  0.140  0.065
vn  0.0  0.0 -1.0
vn  0.0  0.0  1.0
vn -1.0  0.0  0.0
vn  1.0  0.0  0.0
vn  0.0 -1.0  0.0
vn  0.0  1.0  0.0
f 1//1 2//1 3//1
f 1//1 3//1 4//1
f 5//2 8//2 7//2
f 5//2 7//2 6//2
f 1//3 4//3 8//3
f 1//3 8//3 5//3
f 2//4 6//4 7//4
f 2//4 7//4 3//4
f 1//5 5//5 6//5
f 1//5 6//5 2//5
f 4//6 3//6 7//6
f 4//6 7//6 8//6
